A [[petition]] for '''adverse abandonment''' is filed by a party other than the [[owner]] of a [[railroad]] asking a [[court]] or a state board to declare the land abandoned by the railroad.{{citation needed|date=March 2014}}  Most railroad[[Right-of-way (transportation) | rights of way]] are held in [[easement]], so that the land must revert to the original owners if the tracks are removed.{{citation needed|date=March 2014}}

